JOHANNESBURG - A group of women who were allegedly forced to strip and searched after menstrual blood was found at their workplace have spoken out. The women, who work at a Topbet franchise in Germiston, Johannesburg told eNCA that during the strip search, their private parts were probed. They say the incident happened at the end of January and they feel violated and traumatised. The company has responded to the incident, saying it is horrified to hear what has happened but has been advised not to comment on the issue. Watch the interview with the affected women in the video gallery above. eNCA